---
import SeoLandingLayout from "../components/SeoLandingLayout.astro";

const page = {
  title: "Personalized Makeup Recommendations — AI-Powered Style Matching",
  description:
    "Get makeup recommendations tailored to your skin tone, face shape, and the occasion you're getting ready for. No more guessing what looks good on you.",
  faq: [
    {
      q: "How are recommendations personalized?",
      a: "The AI analyzes your skin undertone (warm/cool/neutral), face shape, eye shape, and feature proportions. It then matches these features against our makeup style catalog and recommends styles that naturally complement your coloring and bone structure.",
    },
    {
      q: "Can I get recommendations for a specific occasion?",
      a: "Yes. After your initial diagnosis, you can select a scenario — commute, interview, date night, photo, event — and the AI will recommend styles from its catalog that work best for that specific context and your features.",
    },
    {
      q: "Do recommendations include product suggestions?",
      a: "Yes. Each recommended style comes with product recommendations at three budget tiers (drugstore, mid-range, premium), matched to your skin tone. You also get honest advice on what products to skip.",
    },
  ],
  relatedLinks: [
    { label: "AI Beauty Advisor", url: "/ai-beauty-advisor" },
    { label: "Soft Glam Makeup", url: "/looks/soft-glam" },
    { label: "Makeup for Your Face Shape", url: "/for/face-shape-contour" },
    { label: "Personal Color Diagnosis", url: "/diagnosis" },
  ],
};
---

<SeoLandingLayout {...page}>
  <Fragment slot="hero">
    <h1>Personalized Makeup Recommendations That Fit Your Face</h1>
    <p>
      Stop asking friends what shade looks good. Get AI-powered makeup
      recommendations based on your actual skin tone, face shape, and the
      occasion — with tutorials and product picks included.
    </p>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="seo-content">
    <h2>The Problem With Generic Makeup Advice</h2>
    <p>
      "Everyone needs a nude lipstick." "Soft glam works for every occasion."
      "Contour here, highlight there." This advice assumes all faces are the
      same. They're not.
    </p>
    <p>
      A nude lipstick that flatters warm undertones will look chalky on cool
      undertones. A contour technique for oval faces will look harsh on square
      faces. And a soft glam eye look designed for almond eyes will vanish on
      hooded eyes.
    </p>
    <p>
      Personalized recommendations solve this by starting with <strong
        >your face</strong
      > and working outward — instead of starting with a trend and hoping it works
      on you.
    </p>

    <h2>How the AI Matches Styles to Your Face</h2>
    <p>
      The recommendation engine uses a framework similar to what professional
      color analysts and makeup artists use in person:
    </p>

    <table class="compare-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Analysis Dimension</th>
          <th>What It Determines</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Skin Undertone</strong></td>
          <td
            >Warm, cool, or neutral — which makeup shades harmonize vs. clash</td
          >
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Face Shape</strong></td>
          <td
            >Oval, round, square, heart, diamond — where to place blush and
            contour</td
          >
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Eye Shape</strong></td>
          <td
            >Hooded, almond, deep-set, round — which eyeshadow techniques work</td
          >
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Feature Proportions</strong></td>
          <td
            >Lip fullness, brow bone, cheekbone prominence — where to emphasize
            or soften</td
          >
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Color Season</strong></td>
          <td
            >Based on the 12-season system — your most flattering makeup palette</td
          >
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>What You Receive</h2>
    <p>After the analysis, you get:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>3 style recommendations</strong> — each with a try-on image showing
        the style on your face
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>A detailed diagnosis report</strong> — explaining your undertone,
        face shape, and color season
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>A personalized tutorial</strong> — when you pick a style, you get
        step-by-step instructions adapted to your features
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Product recommendations</strong> — real SKUs at three budget tiers,
        plus a "skip this" list to save money
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Start Free, Upgrade When Ready</h2>
    <p>
      The free plan gives you 3 full recommendation sessions per month — enough
      to validate that the AI actually understands your face. If you like the
      results, upgrade to Pro for unlimited access and high-definition try-on
      images.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-cta" slot="cta">
    <div class="seo-cta-inner">
      <h2>Get Your Personalized Recommendations</h2>
      <p>3 free sessions — no credit card, no download.</p>
      <a href="/tryon" class="cta-btn">Start Free</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-related" slot="related">
    <div class="related-inner">
      <h3>Explore More</h3>
      <ul class="related-list">
        {
          page.relatedLinks.map((link) => (
            <li>
              <a href={link.url}>{link.label}</a>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</SeoLandingLayout>
